1
00:00:51,843 --> 00:00:52,844
What?

2
00:00:54,179 --> 00:00:56,264
Should we tell Loki now?

3
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:59,350
Yes. He needs to know.

4
00:00:59,559 --> 00:01:01,978
We checked Bastien's call logs.

5
00:01:02,103 --> 00:01:06,232
And there were a couple of matches
for Jamie's number combinations.

6
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:09,611
So, what, should we call the number?

7
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:11,380
Oh, why is this back?

8
00:01:11,404 --> 00:01:13,591
This website should be banned for life.

9
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:15,366
No to fake news peddlers!

10
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:19,370
Can deception ever justify
the pursuit of truth?

11
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:25,794
X usually represents kiss
and O represents hug.

12
00:01:26,170 --> 00:01:29,964
Sometimes, the greatest threat
is not the enemy we see.

13
00:01:30,091 --> 00:01:32,385
Shall we cut to the chase,
why are you here?

14
00:01:34,094 --> 00:01:35,220
Isn't it obvious?

15
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:39,099
I just wanted to say hello
to my younger brother.

16
00:01:39,318 --> 00:01:40,903
We're currently busy at the moment.

17
00:01:41,534 --> 00:01:46,164
I just wanted to ask
if Jamie passed by here.

18
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:48,024
Or do you know where she went?

19
00:01:48,233 --> 00:01:51,153
Our club's newest member is missing.

20
00:01:52,028 --> 00:01:53,947
We fear that she's been abducted.

21
00:01:54,489 --> 00:01:57,033
The code you left
could lead us to her location.

22
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:00,328
While the execom and campus police
are searching the school buildings,

23
00:02:01,371 --> 00:02:02,723
let's try cracking the code again.

24
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:05,834
If Moriarty chose a cipher
that I'm not aware of,

25
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:07,502
he got me in this one.

26
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:11,004
Listen

27
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:13,967
maybe it's not one step back.

28
00:02:16,553 --> 00:02:17,720
Jamie?

29
00:02:18,304 --> 00:02:19,304
Jamie?

30
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:23,911
- Jamie!
- Jamie!

31
00:02:23,935 --> 00:02:24,995
- Oh, my God.
- Jamie!

32
00:02:25,019 --> 00:02:26,247
- Loki!
- Jamie!

33
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:27,438
Loki, she's bleeding.

34
00:02:29,524 --> 00:02:30,524
Wait.

35
00:02:30,942 --> 00:02:33,194
Do you think he has anything
to do with this?

36
00:02:38,491 --> 00:02:39,659
Hello.

37
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:47,394
Lorelei.

38
00:02:47,418 --> 00:02:49,544
I am Moriarty.

39
00:02:56,092 --> 00:02:57,093
Go ahead.

40
00:02:57,552 --> 00:02:59,721
- Hit him.
- He's weird.

41
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:02,390
- What is he doing?
- He's focusing.

42
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:03,725
Oops.

43
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:06,686
- Sorry, weirdo!
- Such a weirdo.

44
00:03:12,483 --> 00:03:15,028
Hey! Mind if I sit beside you?

45
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,572
I'll just sit beside you. Is it okay?

46
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:19,239
Let's go!

47
00:03:19,324 --> 00:03:20,992
Just ignore them.

48
00:03:21,618 --> 00:03:25,764
You know, you won't gain anything
if you still engage with them.

49
00:03:25,788 --> 00:03:27,457
He's weird, right?

50
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:30,043
By the way, I'm Rhiannon.

51
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:31,711
You can call me Rhea.

52
00:03:35,506 --> 00:03:36,506
Loki.

53
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,426
Nice to meet you, Loki.

54
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,219
Loki...

55
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:42,722
Nice name.

56
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:46,684
You're bored, aren't you?
I've seen this before.

57
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:52,273
I can do this too. Look.

58
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:56,027
Look, I'll make one too,
so he won't feel sad anymore.

59
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:58,488
Ta-da!

60
00:04:00,156 --> 00:04:02,700
If you have a bird, I've got a duck.

61
00:04:03,368 --> 00:04:05,662
Look, they're friends now.

62
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:09,373
Loki!

63
00:04:09,457 --> 00:04:10,657
Do you already have a partner?

64
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:13,753
Do you already have a partner
for our research? In Psych?

65
00:04:14,504 --> 00:04:16,714
You don't have one yet?
Let's be partners then!

66
00:04:18,174 --> 00:04:20,635
I don't think you'd want the topic
I'd prefer researching on.

67
00:04:21,010 --> 00:04:23,330
It would be better if you just find
another member instead.

68
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:25,932
Why? What topic do you want?

69
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:27,892
Memory of a murder.

70
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:31,604
I'd like to know how killer's think.

71
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:35,275
Interesting topic.

72
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:39,529
I've been watching a documentary
about Jeffrey Dahmer recently.

73
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:44,534
That's why I ended up researching
schizotypal personality disorder.

74
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:48,496
I feel like I could contribute a lot
to that research.

75
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:52,083
Actually, I don't want it to be
“just a mere research paper.”

76
00:04:53,251 --> 00:04:54,585
I have a bigger plans.

77
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,171
I want to help people solve mysteries.

78
00:04:57,463 --> 00:04:59,966
Especially if their lives are at stake.

79
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:04,137
That's actually a great idea.

80
00:05:04,971 --> 00:05:06,014
That's nice.

81
00:05:06,743 --> 00:05:08,411
I just need to find a way to do this,

82
00:05:09,272 --> 00:05:10,773
even if I'm just a student.

83
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:13,455
And even if I'm not in the campus police.

84
00:05:16,733 --> 00:05:19,819
So, what if we start our own club?

85
00:05:20,111 --> 00:05:20,964
Yeah.

86
00:05:20,988 --> 00:05:25,408
Like a mystery-solving
investigative organization.

87
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:30,330
But our primary market will be students
here at Clark University first.

88
00:05:30,538 --> 00:05:34,709
So that once we get popular,
we can open it to the general public.

89
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:36,947
Isn't it exciting?

90
00:05:38,564 --> 00:05:40,816
So, what, are we partners?

91
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:44,593
Okay.

92
00:05:45,094 --> 00:05:47,138
Let's go! I'm excited!

93
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,713
What should we name our club?

94
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:53,643
We'll solve mysteries,
and we'll be partners.

95
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:05,388
Hi, seatmate. Mind if I sit here?

96
00:06:12,580 --> 00:06:13,623
Can I try?

97
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:24,675
You sure are good with numbers, huh?

98
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:28,971
Of course! Math's my favorite.

99
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:34,644
All puzzles involving numbers
are easy for me.

100
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:40,149
You know, if you like puzzles,
we'll get along just fine!

101
00:06:58,376 --> 00:06:59,419
Rhea?

102
00:07:02,004 --> 00:07:03,172
Rhea?

103
00:07:18,104 --> 00:07:19,104
No.

104
00:07:20,857 --> 00:07:21,857
No!

105
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,735
No! No!

106
00:07:26,487 --> 00:07:27,487
No!

107
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:29,365
Rhea, Rhea.

108
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:30,867
Rhea!

109
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:32,534
No!

110
00:07:33,619 --> 00:07:34,704
Rhea!

111
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:55,265
No.

112
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:56,850
Rhea.

113
00:07:58,603 --> 00:08:00,521
No. No.

114
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:04,859
♪ Shadows ♪

115
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:08,488
♪ In the dark are crawling ♪

116
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:13,218
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way ♪

117
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:16,787
♪ As if the line could not be crossed ♪

118
00:08:17,747 --> 00:08:21,310
♪ To every scream and every tremor ♪

119
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:24,480
♪ These walls remain the only witness ♪

120
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:27,441
♪ Every noise is etched in here ♪

121
00:08:27,465 --> 00:08:31,969
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory ♪

122
00:08:33,346 --> 00:08:35,473
♪ Heed the warnings ♪

123
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:39,101
♪ The threats poised to strike ♪

124
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:43,856
♪ For this world ♪

125
00:08:44,524 --> 00:08:47,127
♪ is not what you imagined ♪

126
00:08:47,151 --> 00:08:49,612
♪ Heed the warnings ♪

127
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:52,740
♪ Open up your eyes ♪

128
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:57,578
♪ For this world ♪

129
00:08:58,287 --> 00:09:00,807
♪ is not what you imagined ♪

130
00:09:00,831 --> 00:09:05,670
♪ Heed the warnings ♪

131
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:11,092
I am Moriarty.

132
00:09:28,526 --> 00:09:29,986
Stein Alberts?

133
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:32,989
How did that happen?

134
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:36,802
Can't you believe it?

135
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:40,580
That the weakling math prodigy
you helped

136
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:42,248
is Moriarty?

137
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:46,478
Since your club is good
at solving problems,

138
00:09:46,502 --> 00:09:48,045
I came here.

139
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,982
I have a student,

140
00:09:50,006 --> 00:09:53,360
Stein Alberts, 3rd year, B.S Math.

141
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,136
Actually, he's really good.

142
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:56,929
Stein's a topnotcher.

143
00:09:57,346 --> 00:09:59,015
- He has friends?
- Mm-hmm.

144
00:09:59,181 --> 00:10:01,058
He's apparently really smart,

145
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:03,728
that's why only a few can relate to them.

146
00:10:03,936 --> 00:10:06,856
When they talk, they speak in codes.

147
00:10:07,064 --> 00:10:08,190
What sort of codes?

148
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:09,751
A series of numbers.

149
00:10:09,775 --> 00:10:11,986
But usually, it's Morse code.

150
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:14,780
I wonder what they're talking about?

151
00:10:14,989 --> 00:10:17,366
Why does it have to be encrypted?

152
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:20,286
Is it really that confidential?

153
00:10:21,203 --> 00:10:23,432
If they're hiding something like that,

154
00:10:23,456 --> 00:10:26,667
it means there's something
they really don't want the public to know.

155
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:29,479
The victim is probably the kind of person

156
00:10:29,503 --> 00:10:33,591
who doesn't like to share anything
about their private life.

157
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:38,512
Do you think Moriarty
has something to do with this?

158
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:42,850
So, what? Should we assume
they're here to investigate?

159
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:47,855
Oh, sorry, I didn't get to thank you
and introduce myself in person, but

160
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:51,484
I'm Stein Alberts
and I'm pleased to meet the two of you.

161
00:10:51,734 --> 00:10:55,154
If you need help,
especially with numbers, I can help.

162
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:58,032
It's the least I can do
to repay you for saving me.

163
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:04,747
What's a math prodigy like Stein
doing in the Repertory Club?

164
00:11:05,623 --> 00:11:08,167
Yeah. I'm also wondering.

165
00:11:09,251 --> 00:11:10,878
So you're always in front of the stage,

166
00:11:11,212 --> 00:11:14,382
watching the production
from the audience's point of view.

167
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:16,424
Right?

168
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:18,719
Are you interrogating me right now?

169
00:11:19,387 --> 00:11:22,598
Or am I a suspect to you now?

170
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:28,646
Just because I'm good at math
doesn't mean I can't be creative.

171
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:31,399
Right?

172
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:41,867
The first time we met,

173
00:11:42,368 --> 00:11:45,329
the venue was dark, scary,

174
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:48,082
It's not conducive for conversation, is it?

175
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:52,712
But the environment is more relaxed now.

176
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:55,840
We can talk all night now.

177
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,259
Nothing can stop us now.

178
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:00,845
How did you know we're here?

179
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:06,142
What kind of question is that, Loki?

180
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:11,439
So you seriously think he's Moriarty?

181
00:12:11,772 --> 00:12:12,791
Lower your voice

182
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:14,859
I just don't get why you think it's him.

183
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:18,446
Is it because of the base eight we used
as reference to crack the code?

184
00:12:18,612 --> 00:12:20,990
Or because Morayta
sounds close to Moriarty?

185
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:23,301
- It's confusing...
- Until I'm sure,

186
00:12:23,325 --> 00:12:24,785
I'm not explaining anything.

187
00:12:25,119 --> 00:12:27,788
I have eyes and ears everywhere.

188
00:12:29,165 --> 00:12:33,002
Actually, I know your every move, Loki.

189
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:36,422
I know you visited
the student council yesterday.

190
00:12:36,672 --> 00:12:39,359
I know you asked for the help
of the campus police

191
00:12:39,383 --> 00:12:41,385
in searching
for your missing club member.

192
00:12:43,137 --> 00:12:45,681
Don't you wonder
why I know every move you make?

193
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:49,435
Because some of the people you know
are under my control.

194
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:56,025
Do you hear that?

195
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:57,860
What?

196
00:12:58,486 --> 00:12:59,612
The melody.

197
00:13:01,155 --> 00:13:02,299
Hello?

198
00:13:02,323 --> 00:13:03,425
Why would he dial

199
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:06,619
- the number that John Bautista dialed?
- Okay. Alright.

200
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:09,205
Maybe he's connected
to the mastermind.

201
00:13:10,956 --> 00:13:15,252
Connect the dots
and that point you to Officer Montreal.

202
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:19,297
Thank you.

203
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:34,522
I heard Jamie is still recovering
in the hospital.

204
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:40,462
My men should have activated
the charcoal brazier

205
00:13:40,486 --> 00:13:42,321
before you found her in the props room.

206
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:48,911
That's unfortunate.
There's nothing I can do about that.

207
00:13:54,708 --> 00:14:00,589
What can you say about the fake blood
we put on her? Dramatic, right?

208
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:10,307
What happened to you before,
was that real?

209
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:12,810
Or was it all for show?

210
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:14,352
Oh, that!

211
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:15,603
Well

212
00:14:15,855 --> 00:14:18,607
I was thinking of ways
on how I should meet you.

213
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:23,779
It'd be boring if I just introduced myself
to you like that.

214
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:30,369
So I thought of an exciting way,
with a touch of drama.

215
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:36,542
So, you staged your own abduction?

216
00:14:38,752 --> 00:14:40,212
It did the trick, right?

217
00:14:46,677 --> 00:14:50,556
I also wanted to test
whether your mind is still that sharp.

218
00:14:57,479 --> 00:14:58,856
So you're right.

219
00:14:59,231 --> 00:15:02,026
I planned my own abduction

220
00:15:02,318 --> 00:15:04,737
to see if you could solve the puzzle.

221
00:15:04,987 --> 00:15:08,324
Maybe your skills are slipping
because of your new partner.

222
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:09,617
Actually,

223
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:14,288
I even left my bag in the library
to confuse you further.

224
00:15:34,642 --> 00:15:36,602
I'm so glad that you solved it.

225
00:15:36,894 --> 00:15:38,520
At least now I know,

226
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:43,400
after all, you're still a worthy match.

227
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,398
By the way, Lorelei

228
00:16:23,774 --> 00:16:26,527
I'm sorry about the failed attempt
to melt you into liquid.

229
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:32,217
And congratulations to Loki
for being the hero who's always there

230
00:16:32,241 --> 00:16:33,575
to save the day.

231
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:34,827
Bravo.

232
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:54,763
You seem to be fond of theatrics.

233
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:57,975
Is that why you decided to be
a director in the Repertory Club?

234
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:03,081
Daniel told me that you're like a director,

235
00:17:03,105 --> 00:17:04,982
while everyone is an actor.

236
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:07,151
It perfectly suits you.

237
00:17:07,176 --> 00:17:08,553
Oh, you think?

238
00:17:09,694 --> 00:17:12,439
Well, I didn't really have anyone
to toy with.

239
00:17:12,903 --> 00:17:15,989
So I chose to mess with that acting group.

240
00:17:16,535 --> 00:17:20,873
Don't you find it silly how humans
can be so easily manipulated?

241
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:24,877
You just play your own tune
and watch them dance to it.

242
00:17:25,252 --> 00:17:31,175
They're like puppets,
and I'm their puppeteer.

243
00:17:33,093 --> 00:17:34,970
How could you do such things?

244
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,723
You're just a student.

245
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:41,685
Is this really you or someone older
making you do this?

246
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:46,398
You don't need to be an adult
to play these games.

247
00:17:46,899 --> 00:17:48,192
All you need to have

248
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:50,903
brains.

249
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,923
And people who think like you,

250
00:17:53,947 --> 00:17:56,575
who have the ability to exploit
someone's weakness.

251
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:00,412
You know, everyone has weakness.

252
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:02,664
And it can be anything.

253
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:06,460
Like an important document,

254
00:18:06,919 --> 00:18:10,589
money, compromising photos,

255
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:16,386
scandalous video or a secret!

256
00:18:18,013 --> 00:18:18,908
You'll be surprised,

257
00:18:18,932 --> 00:18:21,201
even the most powerful person
in the university,

258
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:22,601
you can make them follow you.

259
00:18:23,268 --> 00:18:24,561
You should try too, Loki.

260
00:18:27,106 --> 00:18:28,690
Don't compare me to you.

261
00:18:30,234 --> 00:18:33,612
Yes, I sometimes manipulate people,

262
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:35,989
but for good causes.

263
00:18:36,532 --> 00:18:38,200
And that makes you a bit

264
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:40,744
boring.

265
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:43,205
You know, Loki,

266
00:18:43,747 --> 00:18:48,019
if you had only used
that hidden talent of yours for creating

267
00:18:48,043 --> 00:18:49,545
"almost perfect crimes,"

268
00:18:50,587 --> 00:18:52,297
you'd probably be rich by now.

269
00:18:52,631 --> 00:18:56,093
A lot of people want to do harm to others.

270
00:18:56,552 --> 00:19:01,265
They seem good, decent, respectable,

271
00:19:01,916 --> 00:19:05,753
but you don't know they're hiding
something evil in their hearts.

272
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:09,148
And while you're busy stopping their evil,

273
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:11,793
I'm here working.

274
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:13,819
Making a business out of it.

275
00:19:20,909 --> 00:19:24,496
You see, money makes the world go round.

276
00:19:24,997 --> 00:19:27,499
Why would I waste my time
doing a good cause?

277
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,169
I wouldn't get anything out of it anyway.

278
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:52,316
Should I congratulate you
on your "successful business?"

279
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:55,819
And I hope you don't mind me interfering
from time to time.

280
00:19:56,528 --> 00:19:57,946
Challenge you a bit,

281
00:19:58,322 --> 00:19:59,406
so it won't be

282
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:01,240
boring.

283
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:04,995
Oh, don't worry about it, Loki. It's okay.

284
00:20:05,662 --> 00:20:06,914
I don't mind.

285
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:11,126
Just be mindful of the consequences, huh?

286
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:17,341
As far as I remember,
didn't someone die because you meddled?

287
00:20:40,021 --> 00:20:41,731
I hope you don't mind. Sorry.

288
00:20:42,719 --> 00:20:44,638
I've been sitting here for a while.

289
00:20:45,490 --> 00:20:46,616
Anyway,

290
00:20:48,543 --> 00:20:49,877
I won't stop you.

291
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:54,127
In fact, I wanna thank you
for the entertainment.

292
00:20:54,962 --> 00:20:57,547
It's boring to play
the game of chess alone,

293
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,758
so that's why I'm grateful you're here.

294
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:03,595
But you're kind of disappointing.

295
00:21:03,971 --> 00:21:05,681
You didn't even suspect me?

296
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:08,058
Was I not suspicious enough?

297
00:21:17,776 --> 00:21:19,736
I give credit where credit is due.

298
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:21,780
That was a clever trick.

299
00:21:22,864 --> 00:21:24,116
You got me there.

300
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,953
Oh, Loki.

301
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,582
I can't afford to lose you at the moment.

302
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:36,753
So I'll keep you alive
until I get bored of you.

303
00:21:38,255 --> 00:21:42,759
Do you remember the fake abduction plan
you made for your two club members?

304
00:21:46,596 --> 00:21:48,432
Are you close with Stein Alberts?

305
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:54,062
Good thing your assistants came to me
to decode the clue you left behind.

306
00:21:54,771 --> 00:21:56,940
Can you crack that code?

307
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:00,736
The least I can do is help the person
who saved my life.

308
00:22:01,236 --> 00:22:02,362
At least

309
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:05,032
I'm not the suspect.

310
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:09,703
Do you know the Polybius square?

311
00:22:10,412 --> 00:22:12,223
Since you're the Q.E.D. Club,

312
00:22:12,247 --> 00:22:14,374
you should be able
to crack that code on your own.

313
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:21,798
God knows how worried I was
when I learned about it.

314
00:22:22,507 --> 00:22:25,010
I thought someone got to you before I did.

315
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:30,599
I was just so relieved to know
that it was just a hoax.

316
00:22:33,101 --> 00:22:35,270
I'm deeply touched by your concern.

317
00:22:36,271 --> 00:22:38,565
I can't believe
how much you care about me.

318
00:22:39,566 --> 00:22:41,068
You don't want me to be hurt.

319
00:22:43,111 --> 00:22:44,154
Oh. Oh.

320
00:22:50,410 --> 00:22:52,996
Much as I'd like to continue
our conversation,

321
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:55,165
it looks like I need to go ahead.

322
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:58,960
But don't worry, we'll talk again.

323
00:22:59,503 --> 00:23:01,129
The game has just begun.

324
00:23:01,755 --> 00:23:02,923
See you around!

325
00:23:04,216 --> 00:23:05,216
Wait.

326
00:23:06,968 --> 00:23:07,968
Why?

327
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,680
Did you forget to say something?

328
00:23:11,431 --> 00:23:13,517
How do we know you're the real Moriarty?

329
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:23,110
Have you ever kissed that girl?

330
00:23:26,574 --> 00:23:28,367
The dead one?

331
00:23:29,032 --> 00:23:31,076
What was her name? Rissa?

332
00:23:32,953 --> 00:23:33,953
Ria?

333
00:23:39,876 --> 00:23:41,044
I don't think so.

334
00:23:42,347 --> 00:23:43,598
But I remember

335
00:23:45,246 --> 00:23:49,291
her lips were soft, pinkish,

336
00:23:49,428 --> 00:23:51,696
and tasted like strawberries.

337
00:23:52,064 --> 00:23:53,274
I enjoyed them.

338
00:23:53,805 --> 00:23:58,050
But it looks like she didn't enjoy it.

339
00:23:58,597 --> 00:24:00,557
It would've been better
if she fought back.

340
00:25:22,312 --> 00:25:24,022
Oh, shit! I almost forgot.

341
00:25:24,439 --> 00:25:26,983
She was already dead then,
so she couldn't fight back.

342
00:25:30,904 --> 00:25:32,113
Silly me.

343
00:25:34,407 --> 00:25:36,409
I didn't even hear her groan.

344
00:25:46,545 --> 00:25:48,755
Loki please save me.

345
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:50,674
I remember her last words.

346
00:25:50,882 --> 00:25:51,925
It was like...

347
00:25:52,842 --> 00:25:55,679
“Loki, please save me!”

348
00:26:37,178 --> 00:26:38,221
Oh?

349
00:26:38,784 --> 00:26:41,154
Loki, are you okay?

350
00:26:41,292 --> 00:26:42,668
You're still affected, aren't you?

351
00:26:43,461 --> 00:26:44,545
Oh, you...

352
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:47,230
Don't worry, it was just a kiss.

353
00:26:47,827 --> 00:26:49,579
Don't think about it too much.

354
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:51,568
Stein!

355
00:26:52,569 --> 00:26:53,569
Loki.

356
00:26:54,474 --> 00:26:55,600
- Loki!
- Stein!

357
00:26:58,116 --> 00:26:59,367
One more thing.

358
00:27:07,417 --> 00:27:10,045
Loki! Stop it!

359
00:27:11,592 --> 00:27:12,676
Stop it!

360
00:27:13,798 --> 00:27:15,091
Loki!

361
00:27:16,397 --> 00:27:17,606
Fucking bastard!

362
00:27:18,637 --> 00:27:20,639
- No! Loki!
- Fuck you, Stein!

363
00:27:23,141 --> 00:27:24,141
Loki!

364
00:27:25,352 --> 00:27:26,352
Look!

365
00:27:27,437 --> 00:27:28,521
What happened?

366
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:33,151
- Stop it!
- Fuck you!

367
00:27:33,559 --> 00:27:34,894
- Fuck you!
- That's enough!

368
00:27:36,396 --> 00:27:39,733
- Oh, that guy. That must've hurt.
- This Loki guy is really crazy.

369
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,785
Poor guy.

370
00:27:42,202 --> 00:27:44,037
Are people from Clark U really like that?

371
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:46,414
Hey, that's enough.

372
00:27:47,666 --> 00:27:49,125
Oh, my gosh.

373
00:27:55,548 --> 00:27:57,109
Fucking bastard!

374
00:27:57,133 --> 00:27:58,301
Please, that's enough.

375
00:28:01,971 --> 00:28:03,098
Hey, that's a girl!

376
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:10,688
No.

377
00:28:11,231 --> 00:28:12,482
Stop it!

378
00:28:19,197 --> 00:28:20,907
Stop.

379
00:28:33,712 --> 00:28:34,713
Stop it!

380
00:28:36,756 --> 00:28:37,757
Loki!

381
00:28:40,009 --> 00:28:41,428
- Come on!
- Stop it!

382
00:28:43,763 --> 00:28:45,223
No, don't do this.

383
00:29:08,448 --> 00:29:10,617
Hey, help him!

384
00:29:13,454 --> 00:29:14,997
Call an ambulance!

385
00:29:16,129 --> 00:29:17,505
Call an ambulance!

386
00:29:19,382 --> 00:29:22,218
Come on, call an ambulance!

387
00:29:24,389 --> 00:29:26,099
Poor thing.

388
00:29:28,641 --> 00:29:31,811
Rhea isn't going to like
what you're doing!

389
00:29:43,869 --> 00:29:45,204
He's still breathing.

390
00:29:56,419 --> 00:29:57,629
Chief Gareth

391
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:00,173
we need your help.

392
00:30:04,385 --> 00:30:07,639
Loki! What have you done?

393
00:30:23,861 --> 00:30:25,571
Call for help!

394
00:30:27,983 --> 00:30:30,654
We have to do something.

395
00:30:35,385 --> 00:30:37,755
We have to do something, Loki.

396
00:30:41,923 --> 00:30:46,386
It's funny how quickly the roles
have reversed.

397
00:30:57,480 --> 00:31:01,377
We used to be the ones investigating,
chasing down the culprit.

398
00:31:01,401 --> 00:31:05,738
Now we're the ones under scrutiny
for the attack on Stein Alberts.

399
00:31:34,893 --> 00:31:42,817
This time, it's Loki being put on trial
for attacking Stein Alberts.

400
00:32:27,528 --> 00:32:29,632
And I can't help but wonder

401
00:32:29,656 --> 00:32:35,536
if I could've done anything to stop it
before everything fell apart.

402
00:33:11,572 --> 00:33:16,387
Stein Alberts has openly admitted to us
that he is Moriarty

403
00:33:16,411 --> 00:33:20,081
the mastermind behind the string
of killings at Clark University.

404
00:33:20,415 --> 00:33:23,292
I somehow blame myself
for not having the presence of mind

405
00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:26,629
to record their conversation.

406
00:33:31,843 --> 00:33:34,905
You need to expel this student!

407
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:36,764
Do you know what he did?

408
00:33:36,982 --> 00:33:39,575
- Even if Loki explains his side,
- He hurt my son.

409
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:40,869
What proof does he
have to implicate Stein.

410
00:33:40,893 --> 00:33:41,643
My son is in a coma.

411
00:33:41,668 --> 00:33:42,372
- As the brains behind the campus murders?
- My son is in a coma.

412
00:33:42,396 --> 00:33:45,276
- As the brains behind the campus murders?
- Don't know if he'll survive.

413
00:33:45,873 --> 00:33:48,132
- What does a verbal admission.
- Kick him out! Remove him!

414
00:33:48,156 --> 00:33:49,253
Stand against

415
00:33:49,278 --> 00:33:53,037
actual video recordings of
his violent attack on Stein?

416
00:33:54,159 --> 00:33:56,286
Loki doesn't stand a chance.

417
00:33:58,494 --> 00:34:00,055
The office of student affairs

418
00:34:00,079 --> 00:34:04,000
has decided that he will be placed
on under recovery.

419
00:34:20,016 --> 00:34:22,518
What is that?
You're just going to let it be like that?

420
00:34:23,019 --> 00:34:25,748
I have always been the emotional one.

421
00:34:25,772 --> 00:34:28,751
Loki's logic was stronger than feelings.

422
00:34:28,775 --> 00:34:31,295
But everyone has a breaking point.

423
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:36,824
And Stein, the man who is Moriarty,
was the one who did it.

424
00:34:39,452 --> 00:34:45,875
And yet, Stein can't even be questioned
because he is in a coma.

425
00:34:47,335 --> 00:34:49,480
But from what I have observed,

426
00:34:49,504 --> 00:34:51,482
he purposely provoked Loki

427
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:54,175
to make him lose control
and appear as the victim.

428
00:35:01,140 --> 00:35:02,993
And he got what he wanted,

429
00:35:03,017 --> 00:35:07,313
students now avoid us, glare at us,
and treat us like the enemy.

430
00:35:11,609 --> 00:35:13,277
Why is the world this way?

431
00:35:13,945 --> 00:35:18,116
Why those who strive to do good
often end up suffering?

432
00:35:20,034 --> 00:35:21,345
Report that website!

433
00:35:21,369 --> 00:35:24,181
Why would you believe Loki, he's a weirdo.

434
00:35:24,205 --> 00:35:24,724
Boo!

435
00:35:24,748 --> 00:35:26,558
Petition to dissolve QED club.

436
00:35:26,582 --> 00:35:29,293
They have nothing to do with their lives.

437
00:35:42,390 --> 00:35:43,975
You won't stop, huh?

438
00:35:44,433 --> 00:35:46,978
Fine. I'll deal with you.

439
00:35:48,479 --> 00:35:51,023
You don't even know anything,
so just stay quiet.

440
00:35:51,232 --> 00:35:54,694
We're the ones trying to solve the
crime at Clark U to stop the killings,

441
00:35:55,111 --> 00:35:57,530
yet we're still the ones you're attacking?

442
00:36:14,055 --> 00:36:15,367
Should I just stop this?

443
00:36:16,156 --> 00:36:18,485
I mean, I don't even know

444
00:36:18,509 --> 00:36:20,953
what's going to happen to Loki
and the Q.E.D. Club anymore.

445
00:36:37,263 --> 00:36:40,343
I thought you were in control
of what's happening at Clark U?

446
00:36:41,382 --> 00:36:44,176
Then why is this all over social media?

447
00:36:46,477 --> 00:36:47,556
I'm sorry, Mr. President.

448
00:36:47,580 --> 00:36:51,518
I couldn't stop the students
from taking videos or photos,

449
00:36:51,542 --> 00:36:55,320
- using their phones to...
- That's not an excuse!

450
00:36:56,230 --> 00:36:58,100
I assigned you to this job,

451
00:36:58,125 --> 00:37:01,344
so I expect you to do your job well.

452
00:37:02,178 --> 00:37:05,000
It's such a waste of what we're paying
the media and the families

453
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:08,673
if this is how it's going to
turn out, it's embarassing!

454
00:37:10,161 --> 00:37:12,747
This is a huge scandal at the University!

455
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:17,807
I

456
00:37:18,653 --> 00:37:20,404
I apologize, Mr. President.

457
00:37:21,235 --> 00:37:23,375
One last chance, Chief Gareth.

458
00:37:23,796 --> 00:37:26,215
One more act of negligence from you,

459
00:37:26,646 --> 00:37:29,641
and I'll remove you from your position
as campus police.

460
00:37:30,822 --> 00:37:31,968
You may now leave!

461
00:37:51,102 --> 00:37:55,731
Lori, has it already been a week
since the incident at the cafe?

462
00:37:58,311 --> 00:38:00,271
Looks like you're deep in thought.

463
00:38:02,905 --> 00:38:03,905
Sorry.

464
00:38:05,918 --> 00:38:06,975
It's nothing.

465
00:38:07,584 --> 00:38:13,334
Just thinking about our final exams.
They're this week, right?

466
00:38:15,274 --> 00:38:17,401
I know you're thinking about Loki.

467
00:38:18,212 --> 00:38:19,213
How is he?

468
00:38:19,689 --> 00:38:21,650
I haven't seen him for days.

469
00:38:23,275 --> 00:38:25,818
He's indefinitely suspended.

470
00:38:26,847 --> 00:38:31,412
Until the school admin finishes
investigating the café incident,

471
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:34,045
he won't be allowed back in.

472
00:38:34,413 --> 00:38:35,414
Really?

473
00:38:36,745 --> 00:38:39,081
I hope his suspension gets lifted soon.

474
00:38:41,104 --> 00:38:44,649
You're definitely going
to get swamped at the Q.E.D. Club.

475
00:38:47,026 --> 00:38:49,362
If anyone else needs help from us.

476
00:38:50,368 --> 00:38:52,078
After everything that happened,

477
00:38:52,810 --> 00:38:54,391
I don't think they see the Q.E.D. Club

478
00:38:54,415 --> 00:38:56,959
as something that can help them anymore.

479
00:38:57,994 --> 00:38:59,078
Really?

480
00:39:00,983 --> 00:39:02,402
That's so sad.

481
00:39:03,767 --> 00:39:04,810
Good morning, class!

482
00:39:05,217 --> 00:39:07,344
- Good morning.
- Good morning, sir!

483
00:39:07,915 --> 00:39:10,584
Get your books and turn to page 78.

484
00:39:17,730 --> 00:39:19,898
Okay. Class dismissed.

485
00:39:20,094 --> 00:39:22,279
Remember, we have a long quiz
next session.

486
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:23,644
Thank you.

487
00:39:24,070 --> 00:39:25,553
Thank you, sir.

488
00:39:25,774 --> 00:39:28,319
Lori, do you want to come with us?

489
00:39:29,925 --> 00:39:32,553
Go ahead. I'll follow.

490
00:39:32,578 --> 00:39:34,556
- Are you sure?
- I still have something to take care of.

491
00:39:34,580 --> 00:39:35,748
Oh, okay. Alright.

492
00:39:36,791 --> 00:39:38,000
Excuse me then.

493
00:39:38,025 --> 00:39:39,025
Oh sure.

494
00:39:39,577 --> 00:39:40,577
Goodluck.

495
00:39:45,864 --> 00:39:48,450
Lorelei, can I have a moment please?

496
00:39:51,143 --> 00:39:52,144
Sure, sir.

497
00:39:52,876 --> 00:39:54,044
How is Loki?

498
00:39:56,017 --> 00:39:57,643
He's doing just fine.

499
00:40:00,246 --> 00:40:03,457
Sorry, I'm hesitating to ask.

500
00:40:04,310 --> 00:40:06,395
I just can't help worrying.

501
00:40:07,365 --> 00:40:09,534
I heard Stein is still in the hospital.

502
00:40:10,199 --> 00:40:12,910
Unfortunately, he's still unconscious.

503
00:40:13,452 --> 00:40:15,788
And no one can say when he'll wake up.

504
00:40:17,289 --> 00:40:21,335
I hope everything gets sorted out
and Loki comes back here.

505
00:40:22,174 --> 00:40:24,176
We still have a lot to talk about

506
00:40:24,338 --> 00:40:26,924
regarding this Moriarty
you're referring to,

507
00:40:27,591 --> 00:40:29,427
and the cases involving him.

508
00:40:30,698 --> 00:40:32,450
I hope so, Prof.

509
00:40:33,743 --> 00:40:35,077
Give him my regards.

510
00:40:36,649 --> 00:40:37,650
Okay.

511
00:40:38,080 --> 00:40:40,541
How about you? How are you?

512
00:40:47,511 --> 00:40:48,973
I... I'm okay, Prof.

513
00:40:50,671 --> 00:40:52,006
Are you okay, Lorelei?

514
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:55,411
A lot's just been happening.

515
00:40:56,766 --> 00:40:58,934
I'm still overwhelmed.

516
00:40:59,832 --> 00:41:03,711
Look, it's not your job or Loki's
to solve crimes.

517
00:41:04,098 --> 00:41:05,183
But yet you do,

518
00:41:05,504 --> 00:41:06,754
for your peers.

519
00:41:06,857 --> 00:41:07,857
And I get it.

520
00:41:08,030 --> 00:41:09,323
I admire you for that.

521
00:41:09,758 --> 00:41:11,844
But remember, you're still young.

522
00:41:12,595 --> 00:41:14,322
You shouldn't carry all of this weight.

523
00:41:14,346 --> 00:41:17,099
You have me and the other teachers.

524
00:41:17,574 --> 00:41:18,867
When it feels too heavy,

525
00:41:19,857 --> 00:41:21,442
you don't have to carry it alone.

526
00:41:22,813 --> 00:41:24,565
Remember, you can talk to us.

527
00:41:26,275 --> 00:41:27,485
Thank you, sir.

528
00:41:27,902 --> 00:41:28,902
See you around.

529
00:42:12,988 --> 00:42:14,031
My teddy bear.

530
00:42:14,698 --> 00:42:16,033
No longer yours.

531
00:42:16,575 --> 00:42:19,137
Have you forgotten that you transferred
this ownership to me

532
00:42:19,161 --> 00:42:20,663
after throwing it away.

533
00:42:27,127 --> 00:42:30,506
They say you have
some very scandalous files?

534
00:42:33,641 --> 00:42:34,767
Impressive.

535
00:42:35,594 --> 00:42:37,656
This teddy bear, poor thing.

536
00:42:37,680 --> 00:42:39,807
It's been there for a long time, hasn't it?

537
00:42:44,979 --> 00:42:46,272
How's he holding up?

538
00:42:47,090 --> 00:42:49,939
As you can see, he's not here.

539
00:42:52,236 --> 00:42:55,322
Well, that's obvious.
But you should be able to tell me now.

540
00:42:58,242 --> 00:42:59,242
Okay well.

541
00:43:16,427 --> 00:43:19,513
I have an offer that you
and the student council can't refuse.

542
00:43:35,279 --> 00:43:36,822
That's why I have an offer

543
00:43:37,865 --> 00:43:41,994
to make sure
the majority will be unanimous

544
00:43:42,661 --> 00:43:45,748
in not agreeing to dissolve our club.

545
00:43:47,916 --> 00:43:49,668
I'd like to invite you on a date.

546
00:43:50,044 --> 00:43:51,045
Huh?

547
00:43:51,479 --> 00:43:52,479
What?

548
00:43:52,558 --> 00:43:53,558
Tita?

549
00:43:53,881 --> 00:43:55,758
What does this mean?

550
00:43:56,115 --> 00:43:57,115
You're going home.
